<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 02:08:00 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>Geordie Rose：机器学习的进步比你想象的要快</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/geordie-rose-machine-learning-is-progressing-faster-than-you-think</link><description>&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/geordie-rose-machine-learning-is-progressing-faster-than-you-think2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 02:07:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/geordie-rose-machine-learning-is-progressing-faster-than-you-think</guid></item><item><title>CT 扫描的机器学习分析</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/machine-learning-analysis-of-ct-scans</link><description>人工智能驱动的工具可以解读 CT 扫描的 3D 图像并诊断某些疾病。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/machine-learning-analysis-of-ct-scans.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 01:52:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/machine-learning-analysis-of-ct-scans</guid></item><item><title>具有圆形状态的量子模拟器</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-quantum-simulator-with-circular-states</link><description>使用处于两种不同的高度激发态的原子可以使量子位既长寿命又可操纵。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-quantum-simulator-with-circular-states2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 01:37:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-quantum-simulator-with-circular-states</guid></item><item><title>谐波推动激光器达到创纪录的强度</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/harmonics-push-lasers-toward-record-intensities</link><description>研究人员已经找到了一种可以大幅提高高功率激光强度的方法，为光诱导物质创造开辟了道路。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/harmonics-push-lasers-toward-record-intensities2.jpg" /&gt; 由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 01:22:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/harmonics-push-lasers-toward-record-intensities</guid></item><item><title>光电突触对神经形态视觉表现出卓越的光响应</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/optoelectronic-synapse-shows-exceptional-photoresponse-for-neuromorphic-vision</link><description>与自然界中的许多其他事物一样，人类视觉系统具有复杂的结构和功能效率，科学家难以复制。该系统既是传感器又是处理器，眼睛和大脑协同工作，以比人们发明的任何东西都更少的能源来解析图像。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/optoelectronic-synapse-shows-exceptional-photoresponse-for-neuromorphic-vision2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 01:07:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/optoelectronic-synapse-shows-exceptional-photoresponse-for-neuromorphic-vision</guid></item><item><title>如果磁铁的方向可以塑造生命的基石会怎样？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/what-if-the-direction-of-a-magnet-could-shape-the-building-blocks-of-life</link><description>在一项新发现中，耶路撒冷希伯来大学和魏茨曼科学研究所的研究人员发现，磁场方向上的某些东西可以影响生命分子在最基本层面上的行为，以及与生命相关的早期化学过程如何展开。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/what-if-the-direction-of-a-magnet-could-shape-the-building-blocks-of-life.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 00:52:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/what-if-the-direction-of-a-magnet-could-shape-the-building-blocks-of-life</guid></item><item><title>自旋玻璃从有序到混沌的完整演变</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-complete-evolution-of-spin-glass-from-order-to-chaos</link><description>当所有基本粒子似乎都遵循严格有序的物理定律时，为什么我们的宇宙充满了无序？无序和明显的混乱背后是否存在组织原则？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-complete-evolution-of-spin-glass-from-order-to-chaos2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 00:37:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-complete-evolution-of-spin-glass-from-order-to-chaos</guid></item><item><title>美国宇航局费米一睹增压超新星的能量来源</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/nasas-fermi-glimpses-power-source-of-supercharged-supernovae</link><description>路易斯安那州立大学的研究人员利用美国宇航局费米伽马射线太空望远镜的数据，帮助发现了可能是首次清晰探测到来自超光度超新星的伽马射线，这一突破为人们对被认为驱动宇宙中一些最亮恒星爆炸的强大磁星提供了新的见解。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/nasas-fermi-glimpses-power-source-of-supercharged-supernovae2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 00:22:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/nasas-fermi-glimpses-power-source-of-supercharged-supernovae</guid></item><item><title>透视混沌的量子钥匙</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-quantum-key-to-seeing-through-chaos</link><description>来自巴黎纳米科学研究所、卡斯特勒·布罗塞尔实验室和格拉斯哥大学的研究人员开发了一种创新方法，使散射介质仅对纠缠光子对携带的信息透明，而同一介质对经典光保持完全不透明。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-quantum-key-to-seeing-through-chaos2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 00:07:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-quantum-key-to-seeing-through-chaos</guid></item><item><title>量子传感器使用原子、电子和光作为超稳定的标尺</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/quantum-sensors-use-atoms-electrons-and-light-as-ultra-steady-rulers</link><description>量子计算机受到了很多关注，尽管它们还没有准备好迎接黄金时段，但量子传感器已经在做有用的工作。这些传感器测量的场、力和运动非常小，普通的背景噪音可以淹没它们。一些传感器已经投入日常使用，而另一些传感器则从研究实验室转移到飞行测试、医院和现场仪器中。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/quantum-sensors-use-atoms-electrons-and-light-as-ultra-steady-rulers.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 21 May 2026 23:52:57 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/quantum-sensors-use-atoms-electrons-and-light-as-ultra-steady-rulers</guid></item></channel></rss>